|archivedate=June 25, 2017}}</ref>\n| season2       = 2016\u201317\n| rank2         = 99\n| viewers2      = 4.53\n| 18_49_rating2 = 1.3<ref name=\"Season2Ranking\" />\n\n| link3         = Quantico (season 3)\n| timeslot3     = Thursday 10:00&nbsp;p.m. {{small|(1\u20133)}}<br /> Friday 8:00&nbsp;p.m. {{small|(4\u201313)}}\n| episodes3     = 13\n| start3        = {{Start date|2018|4|26}}\n| startrating3  = 2.66<ref name=\"s3premiere\">{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/thursday-final-ratings-april-26-2018/ |title='Grey's Anatomy,' 'Big Bang Theory,' 'Young Sheldon' and 'Supernatural' adjust up: Thursday final ratings |website=[[TV by the Numbers]] |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=April 27, 2018 |accessdate=April 27, 2018}}</ref>\n| end3          = {{End date|2018|8|3}}\n| endrating3    = 2.66<ref name=\"s3finale\">{{cite web |url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/friday-final-ratings-august-3-2018/ |title='Masters of Illusion,' 'American Ninja Warrior' encore adjust down: Friday final ratings |website=[[TV by the Numbers]] |last=Welch |first=Alex |date=August 6, 2018 |accessdate=August 6, 2018}}</ref>\n| season3       = 2017\u201318\n| rank3         = {{N/a}}\n| viewers3      = {{N/a}}\n| 18_49_rating3 = {{N/a}}\n}}\n\n===={{anchor|International ratings}}International====\n''Quantico'' continues to be popular in Australia, Canada, France and India.<ref name=\"season3\" /><ref>{{cite web |title=Quantico edges out The Beautiful Lie |url=https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/tv-and-radio/quantico-edges-out-the-beautiful-lie-20151019-gkctz9.html |first=David |last=Dale |work=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |date=October 25, 2015 |accessdate=June 24, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Quantico (M6) : d\u00e9j\u00e0 une saison 2 pour la s\u00e9rie qui a fait sensation |url=http://www.programme-tv.net/news/series-tv/92145-quantico-m6-deja-une-saison-2-pour-la-serie-qui-a-fait-sensation/ |first=Gallois |last=Gallois |work=Programme TV |date=August 30, 2016 |accessdate=June 25, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107063202/http://www.programme-tv.net/news/series-tv/92145-quantico-m6-deja-une-saison-2-pour-la-serie-qui-a-fait-sensation/ |archivedate=November 7, 2016}}</ref> The premiere episode had 2.6{{nbsp}}million viewers in Canada, the largest audience for a new television series that year. It was the most-watched episode behind ''[[The Big Bang Theory]]'' (which had 2.8{{nbsp}}million).<ref name=\"ctv\">{{cite web |title=Week 1 Final Data Confirms CTV's QUANTICO is the #1 New Series Premiere This Fall |url=http://www.bellmedia.ca/pr/press/week-1-final-data-confirms-ctvs-quantico-is-the-1-new-series-premiere-this-fall/ |publisher=[[Bell Media]] |date=October 7, 2015 |accessdate=June 24, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151023093002/http://www.bellmedia.ca/pr/press/week-1-final-data-confirms-ctvs-quantico-is-the-1-new-series-premiere-this-fall/ |archivedate=October 23, 2015}}</ref> Averaging 2.17{{nbsp}}million viewers, ''Quantico'' was Canada's most-watched drama series, most-watched new series and second most-watched series (after ''The Big Bang Theory'') in 2015.<ref>{{cite web |title=TV Top 10: What Canadians Watched in 2015 |url=http://www.bellmedia.ca/pr/press/tv-top-10-canadians-watched-2015/ |publisher=[[Bell Media]] |date=December 21, 2015 |accessdate=June 24, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161201111203/http://www.bellmedia.ca/pr/press/tv-top-10-canadians-watched-2015/ |archivedate=December 1, 2016}}</ref> It was the most-watched drama series of 2015 in Australia and the second most-watched series overall (after ''The Big Bang Theory'').<ref>{{cite web |title=The Most Popular U.S. TV Shows in 18 Countries Around the World |url=https://www.vulture.com/2015/12/most-popular-us-tv-shows-around-the-world.html |first=Josef |last=Adalian |work=[[New York Magazine]] |date=December 2, 2015 |accessdate=June 24, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170628045632/http://www.vulture.com/2015/12/most-popular-us-tv-shows-around-the-world.html |archivedate=June 28, 2017}}</ref> In France, the series premiered to 4.9{{nbsp}}million viewers (a 21 percent audience share) and averaged 3.1{{nbsp}}million viewers during its first season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Quantico : voici la date de diffusion de la saison 2 sur M6 |url=http://www.programme-tv.net/news/series-tv/118945-quantico-voici-la-date-de-diffusion-de-la-saison-2-sur-m6/ |first=Philippe |last=Chesnaud |work=Programme TV |date=June 13, 2017 |accessdate=June 25, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"franceratings\">{{cite web |title=Quantico (M6) : Twitter pl\u00e9biscite la nouvelle s\u00e9rie avec Priyanka Chopra |url=https://fr.news.yahoo.com/quantico-m6-twitter-pl%C3%A9biscite-nouvelle-s%C3%A9rie-priyanka-chopra-131005684.html |first=Philippe |last=Husson |publisher=[[Yahoo!]] |date=July 13, 2016 |accessdate=June 25, 2017}}</ref> According to a ''[[Business Insider]]'' report, ''Quantico'' was the 12th-most popular TV show of 2016 based on ratings, peer-to-peer sharing, social-media chatter and viewer demand.<ref>{{cite web |title=Data reveals the 20 most popular TV shows of 2016 |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/Data-reveals-the-20-most-popular-TV-shows-of-2016/articleshow/56265085.cms |first=Gus |last=Lubin |work=[[Business Insider]] |date=December 31, 2016 |accessdate=June 24, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\nBy winning the [[People's Choice Awards|People's Choice Award]] for Favorite Actress in a New TV Series at the [[42nd People's Choice Awards]], Chopra became the first South Asian to win a People's Choice Award.<ref>{{cite news |title=Priyanka Chopra Is 'Overwhelmed' After Becoming First South Asian Actress To Win A People's Choice Award |url=http://blog.peopleschoice.com/2016/01/07/peoples-choice-awards-2016-priyanka-chopra-acceptance-speech/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160112005058/http://blog.peopleschoice.com/2016/01/07/peoples-choice-awards-2016-priyanka-chopra-acceptance-speech/ |archivedate=12 January 2016 |first=Pamela |last=Gocobachi |publisher=[[People's Choice Awards]] |date=7 January 2016 |accessdate=May 25, 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:99%;\"\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Nominee(s)\n! Result\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2016\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[42nd People's Choice Awards|People's Choice Awards]]<ref name=\"PCSwinners\">{{cite web |url=http://blog.peopleschoice.com/2016/01/06/peoples-choice-awards-2016-winners/ |title=People's Choice Awards 2016: Full List of Winners |publisher=[[People's Choice Awards]] |date=January 6, 2016 |accessdate=January 7, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160107111117/http://blog.peopleschoice.com/2016/01/06/peoples-choice-awards-2016-winners/ |archivedate=January 7, 2016}}</ref>\n| Favorite Actress in a New TV Series\n| [[Priyanka Chopra]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Favorite New TV Drama\n| ''Quantico''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[2016 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/771305/teen-choice-awards-2016-captain-america-civil-war-leads-second-wave-of-nominations |title=Teen Choice Awards 2016\u2014Captain America: Civil War Leads Second Wave of Nominations |last=Eliahou |first=Maya |work=[[E!]] |date=June 9, 2016 |accessdate=June 18, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6iCCGl4MZ?url=http://www.eonline.com/news/771305/teen-choice-awards-2016-captain-america-civil-war-leads-second-wave-of-nominations |archivedate=June 11, 2016}}</ref>\n| Choice TV : Breakout Star\n| Priyanka Chopra\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Breakout Series|Choice Breakout Series]]\n| ''Quantico''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2017\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[43rd People's Choice Awards|People's Choice Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blog.peopleschoice.com/2016/11/15/peoples-choice-awards-2017-full-list-of-nominees/ |title=People's Choice Awards 2016: Full List of Winners |publisher=[[People's Choice Awards]] |date=November 15, 2016 |accessdate=November 15, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117063137/http://blog.peopleschoice.com/2016/11/15/peoples-choice-awards-2017-full-list-of-nominees/ |archivedate=November 17, 2016}}</ref>\n| Favorite Dramatic TV Actress\n| Priyanka Chopra\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Favorite Network TV Drama\n| ''Quantico''\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb title}}\n* {{TV Guide|779622}}\n{{Quantico (TV series)}}\n\n[[Category:Quantico (TV series)]]\n[[Category:2015 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2018 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:American Broadcasting Company original programming]]\n[[Category:2010s American crime drama television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American LGBT-related drama television series]]\n[[Category:Central Intelligence Agency in fiction]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Espionage television series]]\n[[Category:Federal Bureau of Investigation in fiction]]\n[[Category:Nonlinear narrative television series]]\n[[Category:Patricide in fiction]]\n[[Category:Secret Intelligence Service in fiction]]\n[[Category:Serial drama television series]]\n[[Category:Suspense television series]]\n[[Category:Television series by ABC Studios]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Virginia]]\n[[Category:Terrorism in television]]\n[[Category:Quantico, Virginia]]\n[[Category:Television series by Entertainment One]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2015 American TV series}}\n{{good article}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Quantico\n| image                    = Quantico intertitle.png\n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Thriller (genre)|Terrorism thriller]]\n* [[Drama]]\n* [[Conspiracy fiction|Conspiracy thriller]]\n}}\n| creator                  = [[Joshua Safran]]\n| starring                 = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Priyanka Chopra]]\n* [[Josh Hopkins]]\n* [[Jake McLaughlin]]\n* [[Aunjanue Ellis]]\n* [[Yasmine Al Massri]]\n* [[Johanna Braddy]]\n* [[Tate Ellington]]\n* [[Graham Rogers (actor)|Graham Rogers]]\n* [[Anabelle Acosta]]\n* [[Russell Tovey]]\n* [[Pearl Thusi]]\n* [[Blair Underwood]]\n* [[Marlee Matlin]]\n* [[Alan Powell (actor)|Alan Powell]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| composer                 = {{Plainlist|\n*Joel J. Richard\n*[[Joseph Trapanese]]\n}}\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = \n| num_seasons              = 3\n| num_episodes             = 57\n| list_episodes            = List of Quantico episodes\n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Mark Gordon]]\n*Robert Sertner\n*Nicholas Pepper\n*Joshua Safran\n*[[Michael Seitzman]]\n}}\n| producer                 = [[Cherien Dabis]]\n| location                 = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Montreal]]\n*[[Sherbrooke, Quebec]]\n*[[New York City]]\n}}\n| cinematography           = {{Plainlist|\n*Anthony Wolberg\n*Anastas N. Michos\n*[[Todd McMullen]]\n}}\n| editor                   = {{Plainlist|\n*Colleen Sharp\n*Nicholas Erasmus\n*Daniel A. Valverde\n*Terilyn A. Shropshire\n*Shelby Siegel\n}}\n| runtime                  = 43 minutes\n| company                  = {{Plainlist|\n*[[ABC Studios]]\n*[[Mark Gordon Company]]\n*Random Acts Productions (2015\u201317)\n*Maniac Productions (2018)\n}}\n| distributor              = [[Disney\u2013ABC Domestic Television]]\n| network                  = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n| picture_format           = [[1080i]] ([[16:9]] [[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| audio_format             =\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2015|9|27}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|2018|8|3}}\n| followed_by              = \n| related                  = \n| production_website       = \n}}\n\n'''''Quantico''''' is an American television [[Drama (film and television)|drama]] [[Thriller (genre)|thriller]] series which aired on the [[American Broadcasting Company]] (ABC) from September 27, 2015, to August 3, 2018, with 57 episodes broadcast over three seasons. Produced by [[ABC Studios]], the series was created by [[Joshua Safran]], who also served as the [[showrunner]]. [[Mark Gordon]], Robert Sertner, Nicholas Pepper and Safran are its executive producers. [[Michael Seitzman]] replaced Safran as the new showrunner and an executive producer in its third season, with Safran remaining as an executive producer. \n\n[[Priyanka Chopra]] stars as [[Alex Parrish]], who joins the [[Federal Bureau of Investigation]] after graduating from the [[FBI Academy]] and becomes a prime suspect in a terrorist attack on [[Grand Central Terminal]]. ''Quantico'' initially had two timelines: the present, when Parrish flees from captivity to prove her innocence, and the past, with her and her fellow recruits training at the academy, during which details of their individual lives are learned. The series switched to a single timeline from the middle of the second season onward.\n\nIn addition to Chopra, the first South Asian to headline an American network drama series, the original cast\u2014which changed significantly as the series progressed\u2014included [[Jake McLaughlin]], [[Yasmine Al Massri]], [[Johanna Braddy]], [[Tate Ellington]], and [[Graham Rogers (actor)|Graham Rogers]] as her fellow recruits, with [[Josh Hopkins]] and [[Aunjanue Ellis]] as their trainers at the FBI Academy in [[Quantico, Virginia]]. The series' first season was produced primarily in [[Montreal]], with [[downtown Montreal]] and [[Sherbrooke]], Canada standing in for [[New York City]] and [[Quantico, Virginia]] in the United States. Production moved to New York during the second season, with a few episodes being shot in Italy and Ireland for its third season.\n\n''Quantico'' received positive reviews from critics, with praise for Chopra's performance and the diversity of the cast. The \"confusing dual timelines\" were criticized by some. The series was nominated for four [[People's Choice Awards]], including Favorite Network TV Drama, with Chopra winning two: Favorite Actress in a New TV Series in [[42nd People's Choice Awards|2016]]\u2014making her the first South Asian to win a People's Choice Award\u2014and Favorite Dramatic TV Actress in [[43rd People's Choice Awards|2017]]. ABC canceled the series in May 2018, and it ended after three seasons.\n\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Series overview==\n{{see also|List of Quantico episodes}}\nAlex Parrish, a former [[FBI]] recruit, becomes a prime suspect after a terrorist attack on [[Grand Central Terminal]] and is arrested for treason. In flashbacks, she and her fellow agents (each with their own reason for joining the Bureau) train at the FBI Academy. The present-day timeline focuses on Parrish's strained relationship with her friends while she is on the run and attempting to prove her innocence, even as additional violent attacks take place. \n\nIn the second season, Parrish has apparently been fired by the FBI. In flashbacks, she works undercover for the FBI as a [[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] recruit at [[Camp Peary|The Farm]] to uncover the AIC, a rogue faction within the agency. In the present timeline, a hostage crisis at a G-20 summit in [[New York City]] is initiated by the Citizens Liberation Front, a terrorist group. Two weeks after the crisis, President [[List of Quantico characters#Claire Hass|Claire Haas]] and CIA director [[List of Quantico characters#Matthew Keyes|Matthew Keyes]] form a covert CIA-FBI task force (led by [[List of Quantico characters#Clay Haas|Clay Haas]]) to expose eight conspirators who were secretly involved in the hostage crisis.\n\nThe third season is set three years after the events of the Constitutional Convention. After living anonymously in Italy, Parrish is forced to return to the United States after [[List of Quantico characters#Ryan Booth|Ryan Booth]] shares information to her about [[List of Quantico characters#Shelby Wyatt|Shelby Wyatt]]'s kidnapping by a notorious international arms dealer known as The Widow. In order to save Wyatt, Booth and Parrish recruit [[List of Quantico characters#Owen Hall|Owen Hall]] and [[List of Quantico characters#Harry Doyle|Harry Doyle]] to help them with their mission. Hall invites [[List of Quantico characters#Jocelyn Turner|Jocelyn Turner]] to the team as the former FBI agent has intelligence about the arms dealer, due in part to their past encounter. Owing to the extreme circumstances of the covert operation, the team must retrieve Wyatt at all costs, before time runs out.\n{{:List of Quantico episodes}}\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{main|List of Quantico characters}}\n* [[Priyanka Chopra]] as [[Alex Parrish]], a promising FBI agent who becomes a prime suspect in the Grand Central Terminal bombing case<ref name=\"alex\" /> \n* [[Josh Hopkins]] as Liam O'Connor, a seasoned FBI agent who was demoted to work at the FBI academy as a teacher<ref name=\"liam\" /> (season 1)\n* [[Jake McLaughlin]] as Ryan Booth, an undercover FBI agent tasked with tracking Alex<ref name=\"castroundup\" /> \n* [[Aunjanue Ellis]] as Miranda Shaw, former assistant director of the FBI Academy at Quantico<ref name=\"miranda\" /> (seasons 1\u20132)\n* [[Graham Rogers (actor)|Graham Rogers]] as Caleb Haas, a former FBI agent<ref name=\"caleb\" /> (season 1, guest season 2)\n* [[Yasmine Al Massri]] as Nimah and Raina Amin, twins recruited by Miranda for the FBI<ref name=\"castroundup\" /> (seasons 1\u20132)\n* [[Johanna Braddy]] as Shelby Wyatt, Alex's best friend and fellow FBI agent<ref name=\"castroundup\" />\n* [[Tate Ellington]] as Simon Asher, Alex's fellow FBI trainee<ref name=\"simon\" /> (season 1)\n* [[Anabelle Acosta]] as Natalie Vasquez, an FBI trainee and Alex's former rival at the academy<ref name=\"natalie\" /> (season 1)\n* [[Russell Tovey]] as Harry Doyle, a former [[Secret Intelligence Service|MI6]] agent and one of the CIA recruits at The Farm<ref name=\"harry\" /> (seasons 2\u20133)\n* [[Pearl Thusi]] as Dayana Mampasi, an attorney and one of the CIA recruits at The Farm<ref name=\"dayana\" /> (season 2)\n* [[Blair Underwood]] as Owen Hall, a former CIA lead instructor at The Farm and current Deputy Director of the FBI<ref name=\"owen\" /> (seasons 2\u20133)\n* [[Marlee Matlin]] as Jocelyn Turner, an ex-FBI agent and undercover expert whose career was derailed after she was rendered deaf from a bombing<ref name=\"jocelynturner\" /> (season 3)\n* [[Alan Powell (actor)|Alan Powell]] as Mike McQuigg, an overly assertive and adept FBI operative with several years of undercover experience<ref name=\"mikemcquigg\" /> (season 3)\n\n==Production==\n\n===Development===\n{{quote box|quote=To me this series is like those high octane summer blockbuster movies we used to have in the '80s and '90s with all of the action and stuff, but there's also like this Trojan horse quality to it as well in that within all the action you get to talk about domestic terrorism, religion, politics, and belief systems. If we go to seasons two and three, that will stay the same, but what the horse is made of will change.|source=\u2014Safran's plan for ''Quantico''<ref name=\"observer\">{{cite web |title='Quantico' Preview: EP Explains How 'Lost' and 'Gossip Girl' Shaped the Series |url=http://observer.com/2015/09/quantico-preview-ep-explains-how-lost-and-gossip-girl-shaped-the-series/ |first=Anne |last=Easton |work=[[New York Observer]] |date=September 27, 2017 |accessdate=June 22, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160911134044/http://observer.com/2015/09/quantico-preview-ep-explains-how-lost-and-gossip-girl-shaped-the-series/ |archivedate=September 11, 2016}}</ref>|align=right|width=25em}}\n\nSeries creator [[Joshua Safran]] initially wanted a \"straightforward action show\" different from his past work, which included the soapy dramas ''[[Gossip Girl]]'' and ''[[Smash (U.S. TV series)|Smash]]''.<ref name=\"preview\">{{cite web |title=Quantico premiere preview: Priyanka Chopra, showrunner Joshua Safran speak |url=https://ew.com/article/2015/09/27/quantico-season-premiere-preview/ |first=Shirley |last=Li |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=September 27, 2015 |access-date=June 22, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160420004322/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/09/27/quantico-season-premiere-preview |archivedate=April 20, 2016}}</ref> He revealed that he wanted to do something with a law enforcement theme such as a political thriller about the [[New York City Police Department|NYPD]] after the [[September 11 attacks]].<ref name=\"idea\">{{cite web |title=Where 'Quantico' Goes From Here: Creator Breaks Down the Twisty Premiere |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-goes-creator-breaks-down-827388 |first=Rick |last=Porter |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=September 27, 2015 |access-date=June 22, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160505072139/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-goes-creator-breaks-down-827388 |archivedate=May 5, 2016}}</ref> He based protagonist [[Alex Parrish]], whose complex family history haunts her throughout the series, on a relative of his; Safran wove his own struggle to understand his family member into Alex's desire to learn the truth about her father.<ref name=\"preview\" /><ref name=\"idea\" /> \n\nSafran said, \n<blockquote>\"I have a family member who either is a pathological liar or has been involved with a government agency my whole life. I've always struggled with knowing that I would never know the truth, because there is no real such thing as the truth with regard to somebody who may or may not be telling the truth. That struggle informed the character of Alex.\"<ref name=\"idea\" /></blockquote>He described the series as a sexy romance and a political thriller, adding \"It's like, what would ''[[Die Hard]]'' be if ''Die Hard'' was weekly and was also a soap.\"<ref name=\"preview\" />\n\nSafran offered the series to [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]. On September 17, 2014, the network announced that it had bought the concept for a drama series from [[ABC Studios]] and Safran and produced by [[Mark Gordon]], describing it as \"''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'' meets ''[[Homeland (TV series)|Homeland]].''\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/josh-safran-mark-gordon-team-733837 |title=Josh Safran, Mark Gordon Team for Quantico Drama at ABC (Exclusive) |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=September 17, 2014 |access-date=May 11, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518073429/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/josh-safran-mark-gordon-team-733837 |archivedate=May 18, 2015}}</ref> ABC ordered a [[Pilot (television episode)|pilot]] on January 23, 2015, for the 2015\u201316 television season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/01/runner-quantico-mix-la-crime-of-kings-prophets-pilot-orders-abc-1201356859/ |title=ABC Orders Pilots 'Runner', 'Quantico', 'Mix', 'LA Crime', 'Of Kings & Prophets' |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=January 23, 2015 |access-date=May 11, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150428113919/http://deadline.com/2015/01/runner-quantico-mix-la-crime-of-kings-prophets-pilot-orders-abc-1201356859/ |archivedate=April 28, 2015}}</ref> The series was picked up from the pilot, with an initial order of 13 episodes for the [[2015\u201316 United States network television schedule|2015 network television season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/05/the-catch-jenna-bans-family-kings-prophets-boom-la-crime-wicked-city-quantico-series-abc-1201422660/ |title=ABC Orders Six Drama Pilots To Series |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=May 7, 2015 |access-date=May 11, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150509202533/http://deadline.com/2015/05/the-catch-jenna-bans-family-kings-prophets-boom-la-crime-wicked-city-quantico-series-abc-1201422660/ |archivedate=May 9, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/tv-pilots-2015-complete-guide-764707 |title=TV Pilots 2015: The Complete Guide to What Lives, Dies and Still Has a Pulse |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=January 19, 2015 |access-date=May 11, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150511203853/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/tv-pilots-2015-complete-guide-764707 |archivedate=May 11, 2015}}</ref> Good ratings led ABC to pick up ''Quantico'' for a full season in October with an additional six episodes (increasing the episode count to 19), with an option for more.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2015/10/13/quantico-full-season-order-abc/ |title=Quantico Lands Full-Season Order |work=[[TVLine]] |last=Roots |first=Kimberly |date=October 13, 2015 |access-date=October 13, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151014025344/http://tvline.com/2015/10/13/quantico-full-season-order-abc/ |archivedate=October 14, 2015}}</ref> In November, the season was extended to 22 episodes.<ref name=\"cross\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/11/marcia-cross-cast-quantico-abc-caleb-1201611293/ |title=Marcia Cross Tapped For 'Quantico' Role |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=November 6, 2015 |access-date=November 7, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151108212431/http://deadline.com/2015/11/marcia-cross-cast-quantico-abc-caleb-1201611293/ |archivedate=November 8, 2015}}</ref> In March 2016, ABC announced that it had renewed ''Quantico'' for a second season, also consisting of 22 episodes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/03/03/once-upon-a-time-renewed-for-season-6-at-abc/ |title='Once Upon a Time,' 'Fresh Off the Boat' and 'Quantico' renewed at ABC |work=[[TV by the Numbers]] |first=Rick |last=Porter |date=March 3, 2016 |access-date=March 3, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304093922/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/03/03/once-upon-a-time-renewed-for-season-6-at-abc/ |archivedate=March 4, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Season2Filming\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/04/23/nyregion/tv-as-new-york-growth-industry-quantico-is-coming-to-town.html |title=TV as New York Growth Industry: 'Quantico' Is Coming to Town |work=[[The New York Times]] |last=McGeehan |first=Patrick |date=April 22, 2016 |access-date=April 22, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615161257/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/04/23/nyregion/tv-as-new-york-growth-industry-quantico-is-coming-to-town.html |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/abc-announces-fall-premiere-dates-906876 |title=ABC Announces Fall Premiere Dates |last=Stanhope |first=Kate |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=June 28, 2016 |access-date=June 28, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6ibnIXcKY?url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/abc-announces-fall-premiere-dates-906876 |archivedate=June 28, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe series was produced by ABC Studios in association with [[The Mark Gordon Company]] and Random Acts Productions.<ref>{{cite episode |title=Run |series=Quantico |network=[[American Broadcasting Company]] |date=September 27, 2015}}</ref> Safran, Gordon, Robert Sertner and Nicholas Pepper were the [[Television producer|executive producers]], with [[Cherien Dabis]] as one of the producers.<ref name=\"credits\">{{cite web |title=Quantico Full Cast and Credits |url=http://www.hollywood.com/tv/quantico-60269296/credits/ |work=[[Hollywood.com]] |accessdate=August 8, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808233239/http://www.hollywood.com/tv/quantico-60269296/credits/ |archivedate=August 8, 2017}}</ref> Safran served as the [[head writer]] of the series. The writing staff of ''Quantico'' consisted of Justin Brenneman, Cami Delavigne, [[Cameron Litvack]], Logan Slakter, [[Gideon Yago]], [[Beth Schacter]], [[Jordon Nardino]], and Cherien Dabis, all of whom wrote multiple episodes for the series.<ref name=\"credits\" /> Various directors had worked on several episodes, notably [[Patrick Morris (director)|Patrick Morris]], [[Jennifer Lynch]], David McWhirter, [[Stephen Kay]] and [[Steve Robin]]. Colleen Sharp, Nicholas Erasmus, Daniel A. Valverde, Terilyn A. Shropshire and Shelby Siegel edited multiple episodes.<ref name=\"credits\" /> The Director of Photography was Anthony Wolberg, who provided cinematography for most episodes. Other cinematographers include Anastas N. Michos and [[Todd McMullen]]. Joel J. Richard and [[Joseph Trapanese]] wrote the music.<ref name=\"credits\" />\n\nIn May 2017, ABC renewed the series for a third season of 13 episodes. The renewal was based on the international popularity of star [[Priyanka Chopra]], who made the series a strong international seller for ABC Studios.<ref name=\"Season3Renewed\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2017/05/quantico-renewed-season-3-josh-safran-stepping-down-showrunner-1202092950/ |title='Quantico' Renewed For Season 3 By ABC, Josh Safran Steps Down As Showrunner |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=16 May 2017 |access-date=June 15, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170516162900/http://deadline.com/2017/05/quantico-renewed-season-3-josh-safran-stepping-down-showrunner-1202092950/ |archivedate=16 May 2017}}</ref> As part of the renewal process, Safran stepped down as showrunner but remained as a consultant.<ref name=\"Season3Renewed\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-renewed-abbreviated-season-3-new-showrunner-1003525 |title='Quantico' Renewed for Abbreviated Season 3 With New Showrunner |first=Giovanni |last=Rufino |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=16 May 2017 |accessdate=June 16, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170516213256/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-renewed-abbreviated-season-3-new-showrunner-1003525 |archivedate=16 May 2017}}</ref> The following month, it was announced that [[Michael Seitzman]] would be showrunner and that Safran would be credited as an executive producer.<ref name=\"season3\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2017/06/quantico-season-cast-shakeup-priyanka-chopra-jake-mclaughlin-johanna-braddy-blair-underwood-return-aunjanue-ellis-and-russell-tovey-leave-michael-seitzman-showrunner-1202117775/ |title='Quantico': Priyanka Chopra Among 4 Cast Members Returning For Season 3, Michael Seitzman Set As New Showrunner |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |date=21 June 2017 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=June 21, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170621235345/http://deadline.com/2017/06/quantico-season-cast-shakeup-priyanka-chopra-jake-mclaughlin-johanna-braddy-blair-underwood-return-aunjanue-ellis-and-russell-tovey-leave-michael-seitzman-showrunner-1202117775/ |archivedate=21 June 2017}}</ref> ABC canceled the series in May 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/abc-cancels-designated-survivor-quantico-1105949 |title='Designated Survivor' and 'Quantico' Canceled at ABC |work=Hollywood Reporter |date=11 May 2018 |access-date=11 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\n''Quantico'' had a racially diverse cast as [[FBI]] recruits who deal with their individual problems.<ref name=\"diverse\">{{cite web |title=In 'Quantico,' 1970s thrillers meet ABC's rainbow of diversity |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/act-four/wp/2015/09/25/in-quantico-1970s-thrillers-meet-abcs-rainbow-of-diversity/ |first=Alyssa |last=Rosenberg |work=[[The Washington Post]] |date=September 25, 2015 |access-date=June 22, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160131153809/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/act-four/wp/2015/09/25/in-quantico-1970s-thrillers-meet-abcs-rainbow-of-diversity/ |archivedate=January 31, 2016}}</ref> Safran had wanted the series to be diverse from the beginning, saying, \n<blockquote>\"You're not just watching people who have struggled to achieve places of power and they're there. This show is about the struggle to achieve that. Their politics and their racial makeup and their religious backgrounds are very important to their characterizations and who they are. I really am interested in looking at how every culture handles stress \u2014 and in particular, how people from all these different backgrounds find their place in the FBI, an agency that has historically-fraught relationships with gay people and [[People of Color|people of color]].\"<ref name=\"diverse\" /></blockquote>\n\nThe first actor cast in the series was [[Tate Ellington]] as FBI trainee [[List of Quantico characters#Simon Asher|Simon Asher]].<ref name=\"simon\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/02/brian-lee-tate-ellington-cast-our-letter-word-quantico-pilot-1201369097/ |title=Brian Tee, Tate Ellington Cast In NBC, ABC Pilots |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=February 9, 2015 |access-date=May 11, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150430062344/http://deadline.com/2015/02/brian-lee-tate-ellington-cast-our-letter-word-quantico-pilot-1201369097/ |archivedate=April 30, 2015}}</ref> [[Graham Rogers (actor)|Graham Rogers]] was then cast as another FBI trainee, [[List of Quantico characters#Caleb Haas|Caleb Haas]].<ref name=\"caleb\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/02/rob-brown-blindspot-audrey-esparza-ukweli-roach-graham-rogers-quantico-1201378282/ |title=Rob Brown, Audrey Esparza, Ukweli Roach In 'Blindspot'; Graham Rogers In 'Quantico' |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=February 20, 2015 |access-date=May 11, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150428114943/http://deadline.com/2015/02/rob-brown-blindspot-audrey-esparza-ukweli-roach-graham-rogers-quantico-1201378282/ |archivedate=April 28, 2015}}</ref> It was announced that [[Aunjanue Ellis]] had signed to play [[List of Quantico characters#Miranda Shaw|Miranda Shaw]], assistant director and training supervisor of the academy.<ref name=\"miranda\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/aunjanue-ellis-nabs-female-lead-777628 |title=Aunjanue Ellis Nabs Female Lead in ABC's 'Quantico' (Exclusive) |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=February 25, 2015 |access-date=May 11, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150417162202/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/aunjanue-ellis-nabs-female-lead-777628 |archivedate=April 17, 2015}}</ref> [[Dougray Scott]] was cast as [[List of Quantico characters#Liam O'Connor|Liam O'Connor]], Miranda's former partner and current subordinate.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/hemlock-groves-dougray-scott-star-777753 |title='Hemlock Grove's' Dougray Scott to Co-Star in ABC's 'Quantico' |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=February 25, 2015 |access-date=May 11, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518073434/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/hemlock-groves-dougray-scott-star-777753 |archivedate=May 18, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIndian actor [[Priyanka Chopra]] was cast as series [[protagonist]] Alex Parrish,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/02/priyanka-chopra-cast-quantico-brent-sexton-runner-1201382428/ |title=Bollywood star Priyanka Chopra Joins ABC Drama Pilot 'Quantico' |last=Petski |first=Denise |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=February 26, 2015 |access-date=May 11, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150301135753/http://deadline.com/2015/02/priyanka-chopra-cast-quantico-brent-sexton-runner-1201382428/ |archivedate=March 1, 2015}}</ref> the result of a [[talent holding deal]] with ABC Studios which required the company to develop a starring project for her or cast her in an existing project for the 2015 television season.<ref>{{cite news |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |title=Bollywood Star Priyanka Chopra Inks Talent Deal With ABC |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/priyanka-chopra-inks-talent-deal-758610 |date=17 December 2014 |access-date=20 December 2014 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141219035054/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/priyanka-chopra-inks-talent-deal-758610 |archivedate=19 December 2014}}</ref> ABC casting executive Keli Lee had long tried to persuade Chopra to perform on television in the United States.<ref name=\"approach\">{{cite web |title=India's Priyanka Chopra masters TV's 'Quantico' |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2015/10/27/priyanka-chopra-india-abc-quantico-star/74598088/ |first=Lorena |last=Blas |work=[[USA Today]] |date=October 27, 2015 |access-date=June 24, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160825051849/http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2015/10/27/priyanka-chopra-india-abc-quantico-star/74598088/ |archivedate=August 25, 2016}}</ref> When the actress began considering U.S. TV, Lee learned that Chopra had been approached by another studio: \"I said [to Chopra], 'No, you can't make this deal elsewhere. You're coming here. And I'm flying to India.{{'\"}} Lee went to India and convinced Chopra to accept ABC's offer.<ref name=\"approach\" /> The actress said about Lee: \"I told her, the only way I would do it is if you find me a show and a path which first will put me in the same position that I am in India.\"<ref name=\"meet\">{{cite web |title=Meet Priyanka Chopra, the Bollywood Star Who's More than Ready for Prime Time |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2015/09/priyanka-chopra-quantico |first=Misra |last=Sulagna |work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |date=September 24, 2015 |access-date=June 25, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161024103325/http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2015/09/priyanka-chopra-quantico |archivedate=October 24, 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Priyanka Chopra in 2014.jpg|thumb|200px|alt=Priyanka Chopra, with short, curly hair, in a polka-dot top|[[Priyanka Chopra]] plays series protagonist [[Alex Parrish]].]]\nChopra saw the deal as an opportunity to represent South Asia and challenge Indian stereotypes in [[Hollywood]] and the United States, saying, \n<blockquote>\"When I was in school [in the U.S.], you never saw anyone who looked like us that was on TV. And that was really weird for me because there's so many people of South Asian descent in America \u2013 in the world. I didn't want to be this stereotype of what Indian people are usually seen as in global pop culture. We don't just have to be [[Apu Nahasapeemapetilon|Apu]] from ''[[The Simpsons]]''.\"<ref name=\"preview\" /></blockquote><ref name=\"meet\" /> After being given all 26 pilot scripts which ABC was filming for the 2015\u20132016 television season, she chose ''Quantico''.<ref name=\"approach\" /><ref name=\"alex\">{{cite web |title=Quantico: Priyanka Chopra is TV's next breakout star: Interview |url=https://ew.com/article/2015/09/18/quantico-priyanka-chopra-interview/ |first=Shirley |last=Li |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=September 18, 2015 |access-date=June 24, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160417043057/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/09/18/quantico-priyanka-chopra-interview |archivedate=April 17, 2016}}</ref> Despite having appeared in more than 50 films, she was required to audition for the first time, which she found nerve-wracking.<ref name=\"audition\">{{cite web |title=Priyanka Chopra's First-Ever Acting Audition Was for 'Quantico' |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/priyanka-chopras-acting-audition-quantico/story?id=42302748 |work=[[ABC News]] |date=September 23, 2016 |access-date=June 25, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170222025043/http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/priyanka-chopras-acting-audition-quantico/story?id=42302748 |archivedate=February 22, 2017}}</ref> \n\nSafran was impressed by Chopra's audition, which helped him re-envision the character, adding, \n<blockquote>\"She walked into the room, and it was like the molecules shifted in that way that superstars have. I was very confused because I didn't know who she was, but we all sat up straighter. We're like, this is clearly a movie star; it's like every hair on the back of your neck stands up watching her act. When I went back home I couldn't think about anyone else.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Priyanka Chopra: Pushing boundaries |url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/2015-celebrity-100/priyanka-chopra-pushing-boundaries/41763/1 |first=Karishma |last=Upadhyay |work=[[Forbes India]] |date=December 18, 2015 |access-date=June 25, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107194345/http://www.forbesindia.com/article/2015-celebrity-100/priyanka-chopra-pushing-boundaries/41763/1 |archivedate=November 7, 2016}}</ref></blockquote> Chopra became the first South Asian to headline an American network drama series.<ref>{{cite web |title=Priyanka Chopra Breaks New Ground For Indian Actors In America |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/robcain/2015/10/01/priyanka-chopra-breaks-new-ground-for-indian-actors-in-america/ |first=Rob |last=Cain |work=[[Forbes]] |date=1 October 2015 |access-date=1 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001224135/http://www.forbes.com/sites/robcain/2015/10/01/priyanka-chopra-breaks-new-ground-for-indian-actors-in-america/ |archivedate=1 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[Jake McLaughlin]] was chosen to play [[List of Quantico characters#Ryan Booth|Ryan Booth]], Alex's love interest, and [[Johanna Braddy]] and [[Yasmine Al Massri]] were cast in the final co-starring roles of trainees [[List of Quantico characters#Shelby Wyatt|Shelby Wyatt]] and [[List of Quantico characters#Nimah and Raina Amin|Nimah and Raina Amin]].<ref name=\"castroundup\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/believe-star-boards-abcs-quantico-778825 |title='Believe' Star Boards ABC's 'Quantico' (Exclusive) |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=March 3, 2015 |accessdate=May 11, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518073420/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/believe-star-boards-abcs-quantico-778825 |archivedate=May 18, 2015}}</ref> ABC announced after it picked up the pilot that the Liam O'Connor character would be re-cast with [[Josh Hopkins]] replacing Dougray Scott in July 2015.<ref name=\"liam\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/the-catch-recast-abc-damon-dayoub-bethany-joy-lenz-1201500656/ |title=TV Recasting: Shonda Rhimes Drama 'The Catch' Resets Male Lead & More |last=Wagmeister |first=Elizabeth |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=May 19, 2015 |accessdate=May 19, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150521235911/http://variety.com/2015/tv/news/the-catch-recast-abc-damon-dayoub-bethany-joy-lenz-1201500656/ |archivedate=May 21, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/josh-hopkins-joins-quantico-809508 |title='Cougar Town's' Josh Hopkins Joins ABC's 'Quantico' as Series Regular |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=July 17, 2015 |first=Kate |last=Stanhope |accessdate=17 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150722172843/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/josh-hopkins-joins-quantico-809508 |archivedate=22 July 2015}}</ref> That month, it was announced that [[Anabelle Acosta]] was cast in a [[recurring role]] for a multi-episode story arc as Quantico recruit and former police officer [[List of Quantico characters#Natalie Vasquez|Natalie Vasquez]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/07/14/quantico-anabelle-acosta-abc |title=Quantico: Ballers star Anabelle Acosta joins ABC drama |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |accessdate=17 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150716130351/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/07/14/quantico-anabelle-acosta-abc |archivedate=16 July 2015}}</ref> [[Rick Cosnett]] was also signed for a recurring role as Elias Harper, a former defense attorney-analyst recruit.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/07/rick-cosnett-cast-quantico-abc-1201482075/ |title=Rick Cosnett Cast In ABC's 'Quantico' |first=Denise |last=Petski |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=20 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150721082824/http://deadline.com/2015/07/rick-cosnett-cast-quantico-abc-1201482075/ |archivedate=21 July 2015}}</ref> Prior to the premiere, Acosta was promoted to a series regular.<ref name=\"natalie\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/09/anabelle-acosta-promoted-series-regular-quantico-1201514522/ |title=Anabelle Acosta Promoted To Regular On ABC's 'Quantico'&nbsp;\u2013 Deadline |first=Denise |last=Petski |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=4 September 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905075957/http://deadline.com/2015/09/anabelle-acosta-promoted-series-regular-quantico-1201514522/ |archivedate=5 September 2015}}</ref> In September 2015, [[Jacob Artist]] was cast in a recurring role as Brandon Fletcher, an FBI agent-in-training.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2015/09/11/abc-quantico-cast-jacob-artist/ |title=ABC's Quantico Recruits Glee Grad Jacob Artist for Recurring Role |first=Matt Webb |last=Mitovich |work=[[TVLine]] |accessdate=September 11, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150912154226/http://tvline.com/2015/09/11/abc-quantico-cast-jacob-artist/ |archivedate=September 12, 2015}}</ref> [[Marcia Cross]] was cast as [[List of Quantico characters#Claire Haas|Senator Claire Haas]], vice presidential candidate, Caleb's mother, and the wife of FBI Deputy Director [[List of Quantico characters#Clayton Haas|Clayton Haas]].<ref name=\"cross\" /> In November, [[Jay Armstrong Johnson]], [[Lenny Platt]] and [[Li Jun Li]] were cast as [[List of Quantico characters#Recurring|recurring characters]] who would be added after the mid-season break.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/11/quantico-cast-jay-armstrong-johnson-lenny-platt-li-jun-li-recurring-1201637376/ |title='Quantico' Adds Three Recurring To Cast |first=Denise |last=Petski |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=November 24, 2015 |accessdate=November 24, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306043110/http://deadline.com/2015/11/quantico-cast-jay-armstrong-johnson-lenny-platt-li-jun-li-recurring-1201637376/ |archivedate=March 6, 2016}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the season one finale, Safran confirmed that all series regulars would return for the second season, except for Acosta, Ellington and Hopkins, whose characters were killed off. Safran also expressed interest in bringing back Cross' Claire Haas after it was revealed that she was involved in the bombing plot.<ref name=\"interview\">{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2016/05/15/quantico-recap-season-1-finale-spoilers-simon-dies-alex-cia/ |title=Quantico EP Talks Choosing a Bomber, [Spoiler]'s Fatal Sacrifice, Alex/Ryan Drama and the CIA in Season 2 |work=[[TVLine]] |last=Roots |first=Kimberly |date=May 15, 2016 |accessdate=June 20, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160616131242/http://tvline.com/2016/05/15/quantico-recap-season-1-finale-spoilers-simon-dies-alex-cia/ |archivedate=June 16, 2016}}</ref> Safran discussed the return of [[Henry Czerny]], who played CIA director [[List of Quantico characters#Matthew Keyes|Matthew Keyes]] in the season one finale, since the character was important to the storyline.<ref name=\"interview\" /> In July 2016, Czerny joined the cast in the recurring role.<ref name=\"czerny\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2016/07/henry-czerny-returns-quantico-recurring-role-priyanka-chopra-1201794443/ |title=Henry Czerny Returns To 'Quantico' In Major Recurring Role |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=July 28, 2016 |accessdate=July 29, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160729154944/http://deadline.com/2016/07/henry-czerny-returns-quantico-recurring-role-priyanka-chopra-1201794443/ |archivedate=July 29, 2016}}</ref> The series added three regulars to the cast: [[Russell Tovey]] as [[List of Quantico characters#Harry Doyle|Harry Doyle]], [[Blair Underwood]] as [[CIA]] officer [[List of Quantico characters#Owen Hall|Owen Hall]] and [[Pearl Thusi]] as [[Type A and Type B personality theory|type-A]] attorney [[List of Quantico characters#Dayana Mampasi|Dayana Mampasi]].<ref name=\"harry\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-russell-tovey-season-2-899300 |title='Quantico' Enlists 'Looking' Grad Russell Tovey as Season 2 Regular (Exclusive) |last=Stanhope |first=Kate |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=June 3, 2016 |accessdate=June 20, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606083555/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-russell-tovey-season-2-899300 |archivedate=June 6, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"owen\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-season-2-blair-underwood-908461 |title='Quantico' Adds Blair Underwood as Season 2 Regular |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |date=July 5, 2016 |accessdate=July 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160708154931/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-season-2-blair-underwood-908461 |archivedate=July 8, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"dayana\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2016/07/quantico-cast-pearl-thusi-series-regular-1201785594/ |title='Quantico' Casts Pearl Thusi As New Series Regular For Season 2 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=July 12, 2016 |accessdate=July 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160717135137/http://deadline.com/2016/07/quantico-cast-pearl-thusi-series-regular-1201785594/ |archivedate=July 17, 2016}}</ref> In July 2016, [[Aar\u00f3n D\u00edaz]] joined the series in a recurring role as [[photojournalist]] [[List of Quantico characters#Le\u00f3n Velez|Le\u00f3n Velez]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2016/07/18/quantico-season-2-aaron-diaz-cast-leon-velez-photojournalist/ |title=Quantico: Telenovela Star Aar\u00f3n D\u00edaz Cast as 'Thrill-Seeking' Photojournalist |work=[[TVLine]] |last=Roots |first=Kimberly |date=July 18, 2016 |accessdate=July 18, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160719130033/http://tvline.com/2016/07/18/quantico-season-2-aaron-diaz-cast-leon-velez-photojournalist/ |archivedate=July 19, 2016}}</ref> and it was reported that [[Tracy Ifeachor]] and [[David Lim (actor)|David Lim]] were cast in recurring roles as [[List of Quantico characters#Lydia Hall|Lydia Hall]] and [[List of Quantico characters#Sebastian Chen|Sebastian Chen]].<ref name=\"double casting\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-season-2-recurring-cast-911892 |title='Quantico' Taps 'The Originals,' 'Criminal Minds' Alums for Recurring Roles (Exclusive) |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |last=Stanhope |first=Kate |date=July 19, 2016 |accessdate=July 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160719125304/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-season-2-recurring-cast-911892 |archivedate=July 19, 2016}}</ref> In early 2017, [[Hunter Parrish]] and [[Krysta Rodriguez]] were cast in the recurring roles of [[List of Quantico characters#Clay Haas|Clay Haas]] and [[List of Quantico characters#Maxine Griffin|Maxine Griffin]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2017/01/quantico-hunter-parrish-major-recurring-role-1201883807/ |title='Quantico': Hunter Parrish Set For Major Recurring Role |first=Denise |last=Petski |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119050958/http://deadline.com/2017/01/quantico-hunter-parrish-major-recurring-role-1201883807/ |archivedate=2017-01-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/quantico-casts-krysta-rodriguez-recurring-role-1202042315/ |title='Quantico' Casts Krysta Rodriguez In Recurring Role |first=Denise |last=Petski |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170408214402/http://deadline.com/2017/03/quantico-casts-krysta-rodriguez-recurring-role-1202042315/ |archivedate=2017-04-08}}</ref>\n\nAfter the third season renewal announcement, it was reported that Al Massri and Thusi would leave the series,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-season-3-shakeup-continues-as-original-star-exits-1013530 |title='Quantico' Season 3 Shakeup Continues as Original Star Exits |first=Lesley |last=Goldberg |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170614221658/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-season-3-shakeup-continues-as-original-star-exits-1013530 |archivedate=2017-06-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Quantico: Another Series Regular Leaving Ahead of Season 3 |url=http://tvline.com/2017/06/15/quantico-season-3-pearl-thusi-leaving-dayana-spoilers/ |work=[[TVLine]] |accessdate=15 June 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170615205218/http://tvline.com/2017/06/15/quantico-season-3-pearl-thusi-leaving-dayana-spoilers/ |archivedate=15 June 2017}}</ref> and in June 2017, it was reported that Ellis and Tovey would not return as part of a creative overhaul.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-taps-new-showrunner-rebooted-season-3-as-additional-regulars-exit-1015830 |title='Quantico' Taps New Showrunner for Rebooted Season 3 as Additional Regulars Exit |first=Lesley |last=Goldberg |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170622032457/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-taps-new-showrunner-rebooted-season-3-as-additional-regulars-exit-1015830 |archivedate=2017-06-22}}</ref> However, in August 2017, it was confirmed that Tovey would in fact be returning as a series regular.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2017/08/quantico-russell-tovey-return-series-regular-season-3-priyanka-chopra-1202149160/ |title='Quantico': Russell Tovey To Return As Series Regular In Season 3 |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=August 15, 2017 |work=Deadline |access-date=August 16, 2017}}</ref> In late July 2017, [[Marlee Matlin]] joined the show as a series regular in the role of ex-FBI agent Jocelyn Turner in the third season.<ref name=\"jocelynturner\">{{cite web |title='Quantico': Marlee Matlin Cast In Season 3 Of ABC Series |url=https://deadline.com/2017/07/quantico-marlee-matlin-cast-season-3-abc-series-1202139672/ |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=July 31, 2017 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=August 7, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170806141554/http://deadline.com/2017/07/quantico-marlee-matlin-cast-season-3-abc-series-1202139672/ |archivedate=August 6, 2017}}</ref> [[Alan Powell (actor)|Alan Powell]] joined the cast in November 2017 as series regular Mike McQuigg, an undercover agent.<ref name=\"mikemcquigg\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2017/11/quantico-alan-powell-cast-series-regular-season-3-1202212892/ |title='Quantico': Alan Powell Cast As Series Regular For Season 3 |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=November 21, 2017 |work=Deadline |access-date=November 21, 2017}}</ref> The next month, [[Amber Skye Noyes]] joined the third season in the recurring role of Celine Fox.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2017/12/amber-skye-noyes-quantico-abc-recurring-role-1202221562/ |title=Amber Skye Noyes Joins ABC's 'Quantico' In Third Season Recurring Role |last=Evans |first=Greg |date=December 6, 2017 |work=Deadline.com |access-date=December 6, 2017}}</ref> In January 2018, [[Vandit Bhatt]] joined in the recurring role of Jagdeep Patel.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/01/quantico-cast-vandit-bhatt-seamus-dever-titans-jimmie-saito-sweetbitter-1202244900/ |title='Quantico' Casts Vandit Bhatt; Seamus Dever Joins 'Titans'; Jimmie Saito In 'Sweetbitter' |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=January 17, 2018 |work=Deadline.com |access-date=January 18, 2018}}</ref> On February 16, 2018, it was confirmed that Aunjanue Ellis had exited the series.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2018/02/16/quantico-aunjanue-ellis-leaving-season-3-miranda-shaw/ |title=Quantico: Aunjanue Ellis Officially Out |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |date=February 16, 2018 |work=[[TVLine]] |access-date=February 17, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Writing===\nAlthough Safran initially intended the series to be an [[Ensemble cast|ensemble]], with Alex the lead protagonist, this changed after Chopra was cast.<ref name=\"gamechanger\">{{cite web |title=Why Priyanka Chopra's 'Quantico' Casting Was a Game Changer for EP Joshua Safran |url=https://www.thewrap.com/why-priyanka-chopras-quantico-casting-was-a-game-changer-for-ep-joshua-safran/ |first=Reid |last=Nakamura |work=[[TheWrap]] |date=September 27, 2015 |accessdate=June 22, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170208210047/https://www.thewrap.com/why-priyanka-chopras-quantico-casting-was-a-game-changer-for-ep-joshua-safran/ |archivedate=February 8, 2017}}</ref> As the series's \"face\" and featured in its publicity campaign, Alex dominated the storyline and became the main character.<ref name=\"preview\" /><ref name=\"gamechanger\" /> Although she was initially written as [[White American|Caucasian]], Safran completely rewrote her character with Chopra in mind, tweaking her background as she became half-Indian and spent 10 years in [[Mumbai]].<ref name=\"approach\" /> Her casting also helped change Alex's personality; in one change, the \"jaded and brooding\" Alex became \"fun and warm\".<ref name=\"preview\" /><ref name=\"gamechanger\" /><ref name=\"creator\">{{cite web |title=How Priyanka Chopra Surprised the Cast and Creators of 'Quantico' |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2015/10/how-priyanka-chopra-surprised-the-cast-and-creators-of-quantico-57049/ |first=Amber |last=Dowling |work=[[IndieWire]] |date=October 6, 2015 |accessdate=June 22, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161212170232/http://www.indiewire.com/2015/10/how-priyanka-chopra-surprised-the-cast-and-creators-of-quantico-57049/ |archivedate=December 12, 2016}}</ref> Safran initially focused on the character's dark side, saying that he had never imagined a positive side: \"Priyanka came in and played all of that but as a character who was always in control. And still warm and vibrant because she knew no one was going to get through her walls. From that point on, Alex was the kind of character who can have humor, who can have heart.\"<ref name=\"creator\" />\n\n''Quantico'' was designed with over a half-dozen core characters, in addition to Alex Parrish, for pacing reasons.<ref name=\"variety\">{{cite web |title='Quantico' Boss Talks Sunday's Midseason Return, Diversity and Delivering 22 Episodes |url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/quantico-midseason-premiere-priyanka-chopra-josh-safran-1201723664/ |first=Cynthia |last=Littleton |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=March 5, 2016 |accessdate=June 22, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160719114322/http://variety.com/2016/tv/news/quantico-midseason-premiere-priyanka-chopra-josh-safran-1201723664/ |archivedate=July 19, 2016}}</ref> It was intended to have a [[Flashback (narrative)|flashback]] narrative, shifting between \"the present day with Parrish navigating her way through a class of FBI New Agent Trainees to the near future as the truth and repercussions of the attack emerge.\" Safran also used [[flashforward]]s to spread out the series' [[plot point]]s.<ref name=\"variety\" /> He said in a 2015 interview that although the series is \"intricately plotted\", it does not intend to overwhelm the viewer: \"It is tightly structured and moves quickly between two, sometimes three, time periods, but we made sure that it's not so complicated that it just feels like too much. I like to say that we have a lot of tributaries, but they all lead to one ocean.\"<ref name=\"observer\" />\n\nThe series' diverse cast helped its writers create a variety of storylines and plot points. According to a ''Variety'' article on Safran and ''Quantico'', \"The show delves below the surface into those disparate backgrounds to explore how each character's personal stories influence their motivations for joining the FBI and in their perspective on the search for truth in the terrorism investigation. That offers a wealth of engaging material for writers to mine.\"<ref name=\"variety\" /> Safran modeled ''Quantico'' on ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]'' in structure, with self-contained story arcs from season to season.<ref name=\"gamechanger\" /> Its producers said that each season would have a specific storyline, with Alex the series' focal point surrounded by a new cast.<ref name=\"variety\" />\n\nSafran called the second season more cohesive, mirroring the first season and \"... keep[ing] the two-storyline structure.\"<ref name=\"interview\" /> In an interview, he confirmed that the structure would be \"a little bit of flash-forward, but the majority will be what I like to call the present.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2016/05/quantico-season-2-preview |title='Quantico' Creator Joshua Safran Previews Season 2 |work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]] |last=Tharpe |first=Frazier |date=May 23, 2016 |accessdate=June 20, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821105323/http://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2016/05/quantico-season-2-preview |archivedate=August 21, 2016}}</ref> According to Safran, the producers aimed at a more mature, darker second season which would be \"less confusing\" to viewers.<ref>{{cite web |title='Quantico' Boss on Season 2 \"Reset\" and \"Less Confusing\" Timelines |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-season-2-premiere-reset-932108 |first=Jackie |last=Strause |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=September 23, 2016 |accessdate=June 22, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160924161617/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-season-2-premiere-reset-932108 |archivedate=September 24, 2016}}</ref> Safran had plotted an upcoming plot point as the first season ended, which saw Alex clearing her name, getting fired by the FBI and receiving a job offer by the CIA director.<ref name=\"difference\">{{cite web |title=Quantico Season 2: Here's How the CIA Will Change the Show |url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/quantico-season-2-alex-cia/ |first=Joyce |last=Eng |work=[[TV Guide]] |date=September 23, 2016 |accessdate=June 23, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161028072046/http://www.tvguide.com/news/quantico-season-2-alex-cia/ |archivedate=October 28, 2016}}</ref> He revealed that the season two storyline would focus on the contrasting work ethics of the FBI and the CIA.<ref name=\"difference\" /> Safran elaborated about the differences between the FBI and CIA, saying, \"We're very interested in the fact that the FBI's so much about being honest, truthful and living up to your badge. And the CIA is the opposite. You succeed if you can deceive. So it's going to be interesting to see. It's like a funhouse mirror of what we've seen.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/gallery/2016-fall-tv-spoilers-photos-ncis-grimm-jane-the-virgin/#!17/quantico-fall-preview-2016/ |title=2016 Fall TV Scoop: Babies, Deaths and More |work=[[TVLine]] |date=June 2, 2016 |accessdate=June 20, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160619112143/http://tvline.com/gallery/2016-fall-tv-spoilers-photos-ncis-grimm-jane-the-virgin/ |archivedate=June 19, 2016}}</ref> He announced that the series would switch to a single timeline after the fourteenth episode. Safran said that the second season was always designed to adopt a single timeline after the resolved storyline and the aftermath of the hostage crisis, adding, \"When we broke Season 2, we knew we were going to go to one timeline, because it's about the [terrorist] event, and then it's about what happens after the event. And you can't flashback to the Farm after the crisis is over.\"<ref name=\"timeline\">{{cite web |title=Quantico to Switch to Single Timeline |url=http://tvline.com/2017/01/13/quantico-season-2-single-timeline-abc/ |first=Kimberly |last=Roots |work=[[TVLine]] |date=January 13, 2017 |accessdate=June 23, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170203145117/http://tvline.com/2017/01/13/quantico-season-2-single-timeline-abc/ |archivedate=February 3, 2017}}</ref> He said that the change was also due to viewer complaints that the first season's dual timeline was confusing.<ref name=\"timeline\" />\n\n===Filming===\n[[File:Universit\u00e9 de Sherbrooke - Centre multifonctionnel.jpg|thumb|alt=Long, modern building under a blue sky|upright=1.4|Exterior scenes of the FBI Academy were shot at the [[Universit\u00e9 de Sherbrooke]].]]\n''Quantico''{{'s}} pilot episode was filmed in [[Atlanta]] from March 11 to March 26, 2015,<ref>{{cite web |title=Priyanka Chopra Starts Shooting for 'Quantico' |url=http://www.indiawest.com/entertainment/global/priyanka-chopra-starts-shooting-for-quantico/article_31130cea-c81b-11e4-b940-cff15ecaff94.html |work=India-West |date=March 11, 2015 |accessdate=June 23, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606102711/http://www.indiawest.com/entertainment/global/priyanka-chopra-starts-shooting-for-quantico/article_31130cea-c81b-11e4-b940-cff15ecaff94.html |archivedate=June 6, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Priyanka Chopra Wraps 'Quantico' Shoot in Atlanta |url=http://www.indiawest.com/entertainment/bollywood/priyanka-chopra-wraps-quantico-shoot-in-atlanta/article_ba9311b6-d3fd-11e4-9b24-5be2c3b9d7bf.html |work=India-West |date=March 26, 2015 |accessdate=June 23, 2017}}</ref> with two days of filming in New York.<ref>{{cite web |title=Filmmakers Explain Why They Love Working in New York |url=https://variety.com/2016/artisans/production/filmmakers-love-new-york-1201871913/ |first=Randee |last=Dawn |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=September 28, 2016 |accessdate=June 24, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161106234614/http://variety.com/2016/artisans/production/filmmakers-love-new-york-1201871913/ |archivedate=November 6, 2016}}</ref> It was announced that the series would be filmed in [[downtown Montreal]] and [[Sherbrooke]], which stood in for New York and Quantico, respectively.<ref name=\"mq\">{{cite web |url=http://www.actramontreal.ca/whats-shooting/ |title=ACTRA Montreal &nbsp;\u2013 What's Shooting |publisher=ACTRA Montreal |date=July 16, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150716060201/http://www.actramontreal.ca/whats-shooting/ |archivedate=July 16, 2015}}</ref> The first schedule began in late July and ended in late December 2015.<ref>{{cite web |title=Priyanka Chopra Begins Shooting for 'Quantico' in Montreal: 5 Things to Look Forward To |url=http://www.indiawest.com/entertainment/bollywood/priyanka-chopra-begins-shooting-for-quantico-in-montreal-things-to/article_a27ee8e2-3484-11e5-bb83-170637cfe08e.html |work=India-West |date=July 27, 2015 |accessdate=June 23, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Priyanka Chopra back in time to launch 'Jai Gangaajal' trailer |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/151221/entertainment-bollywood/article/priyanka-chopra-back-time-launch-jai-gangaajal-trailer |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |date=December 21, 2015 |accessdate=June 23, 2017}}</ref> Quantico Academy exteriors were filmed on the [[Universit\u00e9 de Sherbrooke]] campus.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Proulx |first1=Genevi\u00e8ve |title=Silence, on tourne \u00e0 l'Universit\u00e9 de Sherbrooke! |url=http://ici.radio-canada.ca/regions/estrie/2015/07/29/001-tournage-quantico-abc-disney-universite-de-sherbrooke.shtml |publisher=[[Radio-Canada]] |accessdate=4 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005125755/http://ici.radio-canada.ca/regions/estrie/2015/07/29/001-tournage-quantico-abc-disney-universite-de-sherbrooke.shtml |archivedate=5 October 2016}}</ref> The series was shot in Mel's Cit\u00e9 du Cin\u00e9ma studio and on location.<ref>{{cite web |title=ABC series Quantico leaving Montreal for New York |url=https://montrealgazette.com/entertainment/abc-series-quantico-leaving-montreal-for-new-york |first=Brendan |last=Kelly |work=[[Montreal Gazette]] |date=April 22, 2016 |accessdate=June 23, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111232303/http://montrealgazette.com/entertainment/abc-series-quantico-leaving-montreal-for-new-york |archivedate=November 11, 2016}}</ref> Its second shooting schedule began in January 2016 and continued in Montreal until mid-April.<ref>{{cite web |title=Priyanka Chopra shoots for 'Quantico' in \u221225 degrees |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/bollywood/200116/priyanka-chopra-shoots-for-quantico-in-25-degrees.html |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |date=January 20, 2016 |accessdate=June 23, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170107071058/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/bollywood/200116/priyanka-chopra-shoots-for-quantico-in-25-degrees.html |archivedate=January 7, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=It's a wrap for Priyanka Chopra's Quantico. Now for season 2 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/tv/it-s-a-wrap-for-priyanka-chopra-s-quantico-now-for-season-2/story-RKi2U4Gw09nYXn0Jh6JKdO.html |author=[[Press Trust of India]] |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |date=May 16, 2016 |accessdate=June 23, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161030012014/http://www.hindustantimes.com/tv/it-s-a-wrap-for-priyanka-chopra-s-quantico-now-for-season-2/story-RKi2U4Gw09nYXn0Jh6JKdO.html |archivedate=October 30, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2016, it was reported that production would move to [[New York City]] for its second season; according to Safran, \"Season 2 is going to be very much more a New York story.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/04/23/nyregion/tv-as-new-york-growth-industry-quantico-is-coming-to-town.html?_r=0 |title=TV as New York Growth Industry: 'Quantico' Is Coming to Town |work=[[The New York Times]] |last=McGeehan |first=Patrick |date=April 22, 2016 |accessdate=June 20, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427083838/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/04/23/nyregion/tv-as-new-york-growth-industry-quantico-is-coming-to-town.html?_r=0 |archivedate=April 27, 2016}}</ref> Second season filming, which began in New York on July 13, 2016, was shot at [[Silvercup Studios]] and on location.<ref>{{cite web |title=Priyanka Chopra starts filming Quantico season 2, shares day 1 pic from the set |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/priyanka-chopra-starts-filming-quantico-season-2-shares-day-1-pic-from-the-set-2911175/ |first=Kriti |last=Sonali |work=[[The Indian Express]] |date=July 13, 2016 |accessdate=June 23, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161023191457/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/priyanka-chopra-starts-filming-quantico-season-2-shares-day-1-pic-from-the-set-2911175/ |archivedate=October 23, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=7 Things We Learned About Quantico's Priyanka Chopra |url=http://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/news/quanticos-priyanka-chopras-secrets-w446087 |first=Rachel |last=Chang |work=[[US Weekly]] |date=October 21, 2016 |accessdate=June 23, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026183854/http://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/news/quanticos-priyanka-chopras-secrets-w446087 |archivedate=October 26, 2016}}</ref> Filming ended in mid-March 2017.<ref>{{cite web |title=Priyanka wraps up Quantico season 2, gets emotional |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/160317/quantico-season-2-to-end-filming-soon.html |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |date=March 16, 2017 |accessdate=June 23, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170506112807/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/160317/quantico-season-2-to-end-filming-soon.html |archivedate=May 6, 2017}}</ref> Filming for the third season started on October 10, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/priyanka-chopra-is-now-in-rome-shooting-for-quantico-season-3_-24414.html |title=Priyanka Chopra is now in Rome shooting for Quantico season 3 |date=October 10, 2017 |work=Filmfare |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref> Certain scenes of the third-season premiere featuring Chopra were shot on location in [[Italy]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2017/10/01/quantico-season-3-premiere-italy-priyanka-chopra/ |title=Quantico Heading Abroad in Season 3 |last=Roots |first=Kimberly |date=October 1, 2017 |work=[[TVLine]] |accessdate=October 2, 2017}}</ref> The last few episodes of the third season were shot on location in [[Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/quantico-season-3-finale-to-be-shot-in-ireland-118031100455_1.html |title='Quantico' season 3 finale to be shot in Ireland |date=March 11, 2018 |work=Business Standard |accessdate=March 24, 2018}}</ref> Filming for the third season ended in April 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://m.dailyhunt.in/news/india/english/laughingcolours+english-epaper-laughcole/pics+priyanka+chopra+dines+with+quantico+3+cast+for+the+last+time+as+the+show+wraps+up-newsid-85836184 |title=Quantico 3: Priyanka Chopra shares a lovely photo with her co-stars on the last day of the shoot |last=Singh |first=Pallavi |date=April 16, 2018 |work=[[Dailyhunt]] |accessdate=April 21, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n\n===Broadcast and distribution===\n''Quantico'', initially scheduled to air Tuesdays at 10:00&nbsp;pm, was moved to Sundays at 10:00&nbsp;pm due to a retooling of ''[[Of Kings and Prophets]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2015/06/02/abc-fall-schedule-quantico-sunday-replaces-kings-and-prophets/ |title=ABC Moves Quantico to Sunday as Kings and Prophets Gets Retooled |date=June 2, 2015 |accessdate=September 28, 2015 |work=[[TVLine]] |last=Matt Webb |first=Mitovich |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151005204320/http://tvline.com/2015/06/02/abc-fall-schedule-quantico-sunday-replaces-kings-and-prophets/ |archivedate=October 5, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.deadline.com/2015/06/of-kings-prophets-pulled-quantico-move-sunday-abc-1201436369/ |title='Of Kings and Prophets' Pulled From ABC Fall Schedule, 'Quantico' Goes To Sunday |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=June 2, 2015 |accessdate=June 2, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150602231308/http://deadline.com/2015/06/of-kings-prophets-pulled-quantico-move-sunday-abc-1201436369/ |archivedate=June 2, 2015}}</ref> The series premiered on ABC on Sunday, September 27, 2015.<ref name=\"fallspd\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/06/abc-fall-premiere-dates-wicked-city-october-launch-1201440727/ |title=ABC Fall Premiere Dates: 'Wicked City' Gets October Launch On Tuesday |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=June 11, 2015}}</ref> The series debuted in Canada on [[CTV Television Network|CTV]] on the same day as its American premiere.<ref name=\"ctv\" /> The episodes, about 43 minutes in length, were broadcast in [[standard-definition television|standard]] and [[high-definition television|high definition]]. In Australia, it premiered on the [[Seven Network]] on October 11, 2015.<ref>{{cite web |work=[[TV Tonight]] |first=David |last=Knox |url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2015/09/airdate-quantico.html |title=Airdate: Quantico |date=September 29, 2015 |accessdate=September 29, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150929142839/http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2015/09/airdate-quantico.html |archivedate=September 29, 2015}}</ref> The series was acquired by [[Alibi (TV channel)|Alibi]] in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web |title=New US series Code Black, Quantico and the Criminal Minds spinoff find homes in the UK at Watch and Alibi |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a667275/new-us-series-code-black-quantico-and-the-criminal-minds-spinoff-find-homes-in-the-uk-at-watch-and-alibi.html#~pp0zej9PxI0F36 |last=Babbage |first=Rachel |work=[[Digital Spy]] |date=September 8, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150929052252/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a667275/new-us-series-code-black-quantico-and-the-criminal-minds-spinoff-find-homes-in-the-uk-at-watch-and-alibi.html |archivedate=September 29, 2015}}</ref> Season two premiered on September 25, 2016.<ref name=\"s2premiere\" /> After the mid-season finale, it moved to Mondays at 10:00&nbsp;p.m. on January 23, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2016/11/27/quantico-season-2-midseason-premiere-date-monday-nights/ |title=Quantico Moving to Mondays in January |work=[[TVLine]] |last=Schwartz |first=Ryan |date=November 27, 2016 |accessdate=November 28, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161128195244/http://tvline.com/2016/11/27/quantico-season-2-midseason-premiere-date-monday-nights/ |archivedate=November 28, 2016}}</ref> The third season premiered on April 26, 2018.<ref name=\"Season3Date\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/01/abc-midseason-premiere-dates-greys-anatomy-spinoff-deception-for-the-people-american-idol-air-pattern-1202238242/ |title=ABC Slates Midseason Premiere Dates For 'Grey's Anatomy' Spinoff, 'For the People' & More, Sets 'American Idol' Air Pattern |last=Andreev |first=Nellie |work=Deadline |date=January 8, 2017 |accessdate=January 8, 2017}}</ref> After the cancellation, it was announced that the network would air the remaining episodes of the third season as previously scheduled.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/quantico-final-season-friday-abc-cancellation-1202390073/ |title='Quantico' Moves To Fridays At ABC After Cancellation Announcement |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=14 May 2018 |accessdate=15 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nStandard- and high-definition episodes are available for download at the [[iTunes Store]] and [[Amazon Video]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Quantico, Season 1 on iTunes |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/quantico-season-1/id1030601680 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160205131343/https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/quantico-season-1/id1030601680 |archivedate=February 5, 2016 |publisher=[[iTunes Store]] |accessdate=May 16, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Quantico Season 1 |url=https://www.amazon.com/Quantico-Season-1/dp/B014HQBDRQ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151121082632/http://www.amazon.com/Quantico-Season-1/dp/B014HQBDRQ |archivedate=November 21, 2015 |publisher=[[Amazon Video]] |accessdate=May 16, 2017}}</ref> The episodes were available via [[video on demand]] on [[Xfinity TV|Xfinity]].<ref>{{cite web |title='Game of Thrones' Maintains Its Supremacy For The Third Consecutive Week On XOD |url=http://corporate.comcast.com/news-information/news-feed/xfinity-on-demand-top-20-tv-for-the-week-of-may-2-may-8 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170516163502/http://corporate.comcast.com/news-information/news-feed/xfinity-on-demand-top-20-tv-for-the-week-of-may-2-may-8 |archivedate=May 16, 2017 |publisher=[[Comcast]] |accessdate=May 16, 2017}}</ref> ABC video-on-demand released recent episodes temporarily after their premiere.<ref>{{cite web |title=Quantico Episode Guide |url=http://abc.go.com/shows/quantico/episode-guide/season-02 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170310043216/http://abc.go.com/shows/quantico/episode-guide/season-02 |archivedate=March 10, 2017 |publisher=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |accessdate=May 16, 2017}}</ref> Season one episodes were on [[Hulu]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Here's What's Coming to&nbsp;\u2013 and More Importantly, Leaving&nbsp;\u2013 Hulu in September |url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/whats-coming-to-and-leaving-hulu-september-2016/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027140317/http://www.tvguide.com/news/whats-coming-to-and-leaving-hulu-september-2016/ |archivedate=October 27, 2016 |first=Liam |last=Mathews |work=[[TV Guide]] |date=August 19, 2017 |accessdate=May 16, 2017}}</ref> The first season became available for streaming on [[Netflix]] in a number of countries on August 23, 2016,<ref>{{cite web |title='Quantico,' 'American Crime' to Stream on Netflix in Exclusive Deal (Exclusive) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-american-crime-stream-netflix-921941 |last=Andreeva |first=Natalie |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=August 23, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160824135551/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/quantico-american-crime-stream-netflix-921941 |archivedate=August 24, 2016}}</ref> the second season became available in the U.S. on June 15, 2017<ref>{{cite web |title=Quantico season 2 is now on Netflix |url=https://netflixlife.com/2017/06/14/quantico-season-2-is-now-on-netflix/ |last=Olin |first=Bryce |website=Netflix Life |accessdate=June 15, 2017}}</ref> and the third season became available in the U.S. on September 2, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |title=Quantico season 3 is now on Netflix |url=https://netflixlife.com/2018/09/02/new-on-netflix-quantico-season-3/ |last=Frederick |first=Brittany |website=Netflix Life |accessdate=October 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\nThe first season of ''Quantico'' was released on DVD and Blu-Ray on September 13, 2016, in Region 1 by [[Walt Disney Studios Home Entertainment]].<ref name=\"HomeMedia\">{{cite web |last1=Labert |first1=David |title=Quantico&nbsp;\u2013 DVD Date for 'The Complete 1st Season' of the Hit New Series |url=http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Quantico-Season-1/22264 |work=[[TVShowsOnDVD.com]] |accessdate=May 14, 2016 |date=May 13, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517081057/http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Quantico-Season-1/22264 |archivedate=May 17, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical response===\nThe first season of ''Quantico'' received positive reviews with most critics praising Chopra's performance. The [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reported an 82% \"Certified Fresh\" approval with an average rating of 6.9/10 (based on 56 reviews). According to the website consensus, \"Obvious copycatting aside, ''Quantico'' provides ludicrously entertaining thrills from a well-balanced cast.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/quantico/s01/ |title=Quantico: Season 1 |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=September 25, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151129004310/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/quantico/s01 |archivedate=November 29, 2015}}</ref> The series has a score of 70/100 (based on 25 reviews) on [[Metacritic]], indicating \"generally favorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/quantico |title=Quantico&nbsp;\u2013 Season 1 Reviews |work=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=September 25, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160105234111/http://www.metacritic.com/tv/quantico |archivedate=January 5, 2016}}</ref> The ''[[Newark Star-Ledger]]''{{'}}s Vicki Hyman called ''Quantico'' the best new show of the season and graded it an \"A\". Hyman wrote that the show was \"taut and terrifically calibrated ... with at least one deadly effective twist you won't see coming.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Fall 2015 TV reviews: Why 'Quantico' is the season's best new show |url=http://www.nj.com/entertainment/tv/index.ssf/2015/09/quantico_review_best_new_show_fall_tv_blood_oil_ab.html |first=Vicki |last=Hyman |work=[[Newark Star-Ledger]] |date=September 27, 2015 |accessdate=June 21, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410181159/http://www.nj.com/entertainment/tv/index.ssf/2015/09/quantico_review_best_new_show_fall_tv_blood_oil_ab.html |archivedate=April 10, 2016}}</ref> David Wiegand from ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]'' also praised the series: \"The plot is intricate and compelling, the characters magnetic and mysterious at the same time.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=ABC in it to win it with 'Quantico,' 'Blood & Oil' |url=http://www.sfchronicle.com/tv/article/ABC-in-it-to-win-it-with-Quantico-Blood-6518796.php |first=David |last=Wiegand |work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]] |date=September 21, 2015 |accessdate=June 23, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161224094634/http://www.sfchronicle.com/tv/article/ABC-in-it-to-win-it-with-Quantico-Blood-6518796.php |archivedate=December 24, 2016}}</ref> Robert Bianco of ''[[USA Today]]'' rated ''Quantico'' three out of four, calling its cast \"an appropriately diverse group, brought to life by generally fine performances, led by Chopra's and Ellis. [. ... ] There are times when Quantico feels a shade mechanical, in moments when you can practically hear the plot gears moving. But it accomplishes what the opener of a whodunit needs to do: establish a wide range of plausible suspects and spark our interest in the mystery and the hero.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Review: 'Quantico' presents a clever exercise |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/columnist/2015/09/24/quantico-abc-review/72650510/ |first=Robert |last=Bianco |work=[[USA Today]] |date=September 24, 2015 |accessdate=June 21, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161224103410/http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/columnist/2015/09/24/quantico-abc-review/72650510/ |archivedate=December 24, 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[James Poniewozik]] of ''[[The New York Times]]'' called Chopra the series' \"strongest human asset\", calling her \"immediately charismatic and commanding.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Review: 'Quantico' Flips Between Jousting F.B.I. Recruits and a Terrorist Attack |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/09/25/arts/television/review-quantico-flips-between-jousting-fbi-recruits-and-a-terrorist-attack.html |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=September 24, 2015 |accessdate=13 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927215613/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/09/25/arts/television/review-quantico-flips-between-jousting-fbi-recruits-and-a-terrorist-attack.html |archivedate=September 27, 2015}}</ref> Melissa Maerz of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' called ''Quantico'' the best [[Shonda Rhimes]] drama that Rhimes never touched and wrote that \"Chopra's bound to be a breakout star.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Fall TV Preview: Best new shows, as chosen by EW critics |url=https://ew.com/article/2015/09/15/fall-tv-preview-best-new-shows-ew-critics/ |first=Melissa |last=Maerz |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=September 15, 2015 |accessdate=June 21, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823103921/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/09/15/fall-tv-preview-best-new-shows-ew-critics |archivedate=August 23, 2016}}</ref> Rob Lowman of the ''[[Los Angeles Daily News]]'' enjoyed the show and Chopra's performance, saying, \"Although a bit over-frenetic at times, the series seems to take inspiration from a man-on-the-run Hitchcock thriller. Only in Quantico's case, it's a woman, and they have a charismatic star in Chopra. I was immediately struck by her dynamic screen presence. So far it's one of the most promising new shows, and Chopra is someone worth keeping an eye on.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Review: 'Quantico' gets a running start with a stunning Priyanka Chopra |url=http://www.dailynews.com/arts-and-entertainment/20150925/review-quantico-gets-a-running-start-with-a-stunning-priyanka-chopra |first=Rob |last=Lowman |work=[[Los Angeles Daily News]] |date=September 27, 2015 |accessdate=June 23, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161211015603/http://www.dailynews.com/arts-and-entertainment/20150925/review-quantico-gets-a-running-start-with-a-stunning-priyanka-chopra |archivedate=December 11, 2016}}</ref> Tim Goodman of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'', in a lukewarm review, found its pilot \"just good enough to make you watch another.\"<ref>{{cite news |title='Quantico': TV Review |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/quantico-tv-review-827460 |first=Tim |last=Goodman |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=September 27, 2015 |accessdate=June 21, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617023120/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/quantico-tv-review-827460 |archivedate=June 17, 2016}}</ref> Although [[TheWrap]]'s Tim Grierson wrote that the show \"provides sexy fun\", he went on to write: \"For a show about highly trained, incredibly intelligent agents, Quantico often succumbs to lame-brained plotting and a less-than-convincing portrayal of its specialized milieu. This new show's fluffy, which doesn't fit so well with the darker, somber tones meant to be struck by the introduction of a cataclysmic terrorist attack.\"<ref>{{cite news |title='Quantico' Review: Priyanka Chopra Scores in Silly Spy Drama |url=https://www.thewrap.com/quantico-review-priyanka-chopra-scores-in-silly-spy-drama/ |first=Tim |last=Grierson |work=[[TheWrap]] |date=September 27, 2015 |accessdate=June 21, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312110641/http://www.thewrap.com/quantico-review-priyanka-chopra-scores-in-silly-spy-drama/ |archivedate=March 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe second season also received positive reviews.<ref name=\"finale\">{{cite web |title=Quantico recap: 'Resistance' |url=https://ew.com/recap/quantico-season-2-finale/ |first=Madison |last=Vain |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=15 May 2017 |accessdate=12 December 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170607054846/http://ew.com/recap/quantico-season-2-finale/ |archivedate=June 7, 2017 |df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Quantico Recap: Protecting the Asset |url=https://www.vulture.com/2017/02/quantico-recap-season-two-episode-11.html |first=Kelsey |last=McKinney |work=New York Magazine |date=January 30, 2017 |accessdate=June 21, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171211225510/http://www.vulture.com/2017/02/quantico-recap-season-two-episode-11.html |archivedate=December 11, 2017 |df=mdy-all}}</ref> Jasef Wisener of ''[[Screener (website)|TVOvermind]]'' gave the premiere episode a rating of three and a half stars, writing that it set up its sophomore season \"effectively\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Quantico Season 2 Premiere Review: The Soapy Drama Delivers More of the Same (Which Isn't Necessarily a Bad Thing) |url=http://www.tvovermind.com/quantico/quantico-season-2-premiere-review-soapy-drama-switches-things-staying |first=Jasef |last=Wisener |work=[[Screener (website)|TVOvermind]] |date=25 September 2016 |accessdate=12 December 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101124107/http://www.tvovermind.com/quantico/quantico-season-2-premiere-review-soapy-drama-switches-things-staying |archivedate=November 1, 2016 |df=mdy-all}}</ref> However, Allison Nichols of ''TV Fanatic'' was critical of the opening episode owing to the \"confusing time jumps\" and the \"head-spinning plotlines\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Quantico Season 2 Episode 1 Review: Kudove |url=https://www.tvfanatic.com/2016/09/quantico-season-2-episode-1-review-kudove/ |first=Allison |last=Nichols |work=TV Fanatic |date=25 September 2017 |accessdate=12 December 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170302220926/https://www.tvfanatic.com/2016/09/quantico-season-2-episode-1-review-kudove/ |archivedate=March 2, 2017 |df=mdy-all}}</ref> The episodes following the winter finale when the show's narrative switched to a single timeline garnered further praise by such critics as Madison Vain of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'', especially for its focus on [[Character arc|character development]].<ref name=\"finale\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Quantico Recap: A Fresh Start |url=https://www.vulture.com/2017/02/quantico-recap-season-2-episode-13.html |first=Kelsey |last=McKinney |work=New York Magazine |date=February 20, 2017 |accessdate=June 21, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170625184643/http://www.vulture.com/2017/02/quantico-recap-season-2-episode-13.html |archivedate=June 25, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"follow\">{{cite news |title=Quantico Recap: Follow the Money |url=https://www.vulture.com/2017/03/quantico-recap-season-2-episode-14.html |first=Kelsey |last=McKinney |work=New York Magazine |date=March 20, 2017 |accessdate=June 21, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170615101904/http://www.vulture.com/2017/03/quantico-recap-season-2-episode-14.html |archivedate=June 15, 2017}}</ref> Kelsey McKinney of ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]'' magazine noted that the show had finally found its groove, writing, \"For the first time since its first season, Quantico actually seems to know where it is headed. It's quite a welcome development, and the newfound confidence ... makes Quantico a much more enjoyable show to watch.\"<ref name=\"follow\" /> In a five-star review of the sixteenth episode, Kelsey McKinney of ''New York'' wrote that \"the show is grappling more and more with the emotions that make us all human, not just the ones that drive the story forward.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Quantico Recap: The Hunt Begins |url=https://www.vulture.com/2017/04/quantico-recap-season-2-episode-16.html |first=Kelsey |last=McKinney |work=[[New York Magazine]] |date=April 3, 2017 |accessdate=June 21, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170617035751/http://www.vulture.com/2017/04/quantico-recap-season-2-episode-16.html |archivedate=June 17, 2017}}</ref> The series' plot lines, involving current political situations, were also praised.<ref>{{cite news |title=Quantico Recap: A Little Too Close to Home |url=https://www.vulture.com/2017/04/quantico-recap-season-2-episode-17.html |first=Kelsey |last=McKinney |work=[[New York Magazine]] |date=April 10, 2017 |accessdate=June 21, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170617035723/http://www.vulture.com/2017/04/quantico-recap-season-2-episode-17.html |archivedate=June 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Quantico Recap: A Divided America |url=https://www.vulture.com/2017/04/quantico-recap-season-2-episode-18.html |first=Kelsey |last=McKinney |work=[[New York Magazine]] |date=April 18, 2017 |accessdate=June 21, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170617040134/http://www.vulture.com/2017/04/quantico-recap-season-2-episode-18.html |archivedate=June 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Critics' Top Ten lists \u2013 2015====\n\n* No.&nbsp;8 \u2013 ''[[People Magazine]]''<ref>Gliatto, Tom. [http://time.com/collection-post/4299686/priyanka-chopra-2016-time-100/ \"PEOPLE Picks the Best TV Shows of 2015\"]. People, 2015-12-15. Retrieved 2018-07-26.</ref>&nbsp;\n* ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]''<ref>Lawson, Richard & Robinson, Joanna. [https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/photos/2015/12/best-new-tv-shows-of-2015 \"The Best New TV Shows of 2015\"]. Vanity Fair, 2015-12-11. Retrieved 2018-07-26.</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\n====<span id=\"U.S. ratings\"></span>United States====\n''Quantico''{{'s}} season one premiere garnered 7.14{{nbsp}}million viewers and a 1.9 rating among adults 18\u201349, the highest-rated scripted telecast on Sunday night opposite ''[[Sunday Night Football on NBC|Sunday Night Football]]''. It improved 36 percent on its lead-in, ''[[Blood & Oil]]'', which had a 1.4 rating.<ref>{{cite web |title='Quantico' Off To Solid Ratings Start, 'CSI' Has Respectable Final Bow |url=https://deadline.com/2015/09/quantico-premiere-ratings-priyanka-chopra-csi-finale-1201555090/ |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=September 28, 2015 |accessdate=June 23, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170622204546/https://deadline.com/2015/09/quantico-premiere-ratings-priyanka-chopra-csi-finale-1201555090/ |archivedate=June 22, 2017}}</ref> The pilot episode was also popular for [[Digital video recorder|DVR]] playback with over five million viewers, a 79 percent increase, for a total 3.4 rating among adults 18\u201349 and total viewership of 12.15&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ratings: ABC's 'Quantico' a Big Gainer in Delayed Viewing |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/ratings-abcs-quantico-delayed-viewing-1201608523/ |first=Rick |last=Kissell |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=October 2, 2015 |accessdate=June 23, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160927204552/http://variety.com/2015/tv/news/ratings-abcs-quantico-delayed-viewing-1201608523/ |archivedate=September 27, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/10/11/premiere-week-live-7-ratings-blindspot-empire-and-big-bang-theory-score-biggest-gains/477409/ |title=Premiere week Live +7 ratings: 'Blindspot', 'Empire' and 'Big Bang Theory' score biggest gains |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=October 11, 2015 |website=[[TV by the Numbers]] |accessdate=October 11, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151013183937/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/10/11/premiere-week-live-7-ratings-blindspot-empire-and-big-bang-theory-score-biggest-gains/477409/ |archivedate=October 13, 2015}}</ref> The series, which continued to do well in live viewing, more than doubled its viewership several times in DVR playback during the season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Delayed-Viewing: ABC's 'Quantico' More Than Doubles Its Rating on Busy Sunday Night |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/delayed-viewing-quantico-more-than-double-sunday-1201632357/ |first=Rick |last=Kissell |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=November 6, 2015 |accessdate=June 23, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=TV Ratings: DVR-Friendly 'Quantico' Steady in Fall Finale |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/tv-ratings-dvr-friendly-quantico-848403 |author=O'Connell, Michael |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=December 14, 2015 |accessdate=June 23, 2017}}</ref> The finale had 3.78&nbsp;million viewers with a 1.0 rating among adults 18\u201349 and a 120 percent DVR increase for a 2.2 adult 18\u201349 rating and a total of 6.7{{nbsp}}million viewers.<ref name=\"1.22\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/05/31/broadcast-live-7-ratings-may-9-15-2016/ |title=Broadcast Live +7 ratings: 'Big Bang Theory' finale and 'Empire' share lead for May 9\u201315 |last=Porter |first=Rick |website=[[TV by the Numbers]] |date=May 31, 2016 |accessdate=June 4, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160601134556/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/05/31/broadcast-live-7-ratings-may-9-15-2016/ |archivedate=June 1, 2016}}</ref> The first season averaged 8.05{{nbsp}}million viewers with a 2.6 rating among adults 18\u201349.<ref name=\"Season1Ranking\" />\n\nThe second-season premiere had 3.64{{nbsp}}million viewers and a 1.0 rating among adults 18\u201349.<ref name=\"s2premiere\" /> The finale attracted 2.72{{nbsp}}million viewers with a 0.6 rating among adults 18\u201349.<ref name=\"s2finale\" /> The season averaged 4.53{{nbsp}}million viewers with a 1.3 rating among adults 18\u201349.<ref name=\"Season2Ranking\" /> The third-season premiere and series finale both attracted 2.66{{nbsp}}million viewers, with a 0.5 and 0.4 rating among adults 18\u201349 demographic, respectively.<ref name=\"s3premiere\" /><ref name=\"s3finale\" />\n\n<!--Please note that ratings tables are supported by WP:TVRECEPTION!-->\n{{Television season ratings\n| link1         = Quantico (season 1)\n| timeslot1     = Sunday 10:00&nbsp;p.m.\n| episodes1     = 22\n| start1        = {{Start date|2015|9|27}}\n| startrating1  = 7.14<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/09/29/sunday-final-ratings-bobs-burgers-adjusted-down-60-minutes-adjusted-up-sunday-night-football/473898/ |title=Sunday Final Ratings: 'Bob's Burgers' Adjusted Down, '60 Minutes' Adjusted Up + 'Sunday Night Football' |last=Dixon |first=Dani |website=[[TV by the Numbers]] |date=September 29, 2015 |accessdate=September 29, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150930221125/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/09/29/sunday-final-ratings-bobs-burgers-adjusted-down-60-minutes-adjusted-up-sunday-night-football/473898/ |archivedate=September 30, 2015}}</ref>f\n| end1          = {{End date|2016|5|15}}\n| endrating1    = 3.78<ref name=\"1.22\">{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/05/17/sunday-final-ratings-may-15-2016/ |title=Sunday final ratings: 'Once Upon a Time' finale, everything else hold |last=Porter |first=Rick |website=[[TV by the Numbers]] |date=May 17, 2016 |accessdate=May 17, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://